volunteers\n: a person who freely offers to take part in an enterprise or undertake a task.
warrior\n: (especially in former times) a brave or experienced soldier or fighter.
welfare\n: the health, happiness, and fortunes of a person or group.
whereas\n: in contrast or comparison with the fact that.
widespread\n: found or distributed over a large area or number of people.
wobble \n: move or cause to move unsteadily from side to side.
young\n: having lived or existed for only a short time.
